<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1122,1473]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
The 
<typeStatus box="[250,298,1159,1185]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
species of this genus remains without re-examination. The describer mentioned that this genus could be placed between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1842" box="[373,527,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Brachypeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[373,527,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Brachypeplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[587,715,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Macrostola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[587,715,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Macrostola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the body 3.0 × as long as wide and glabrous (except for abdomen), rather short head bearing exposed labrum, and also short and convergent antennal grooves, pronotum subexplanate at sides, with rounded anterior and posterior angles, elongate striate elytra and nearly conical abdomen with longest ultimate segment. The detailed original description of both genus and two species (
<taxonomicName authority="Grouvelle, 1916" authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Macrostolops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inusitatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Macrostolops inusitatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grouvelle, A." box="[267,448,1339,1365]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="234 - 256" refId="ref105215" refString="Grouvelle, A. (1916) Descriptions des Clavicornes nouveaux de la Republique Argentine. Revista del Museo de La Plata, 23, 234 - 256." type="journal article" year="1916">Grouvelle, 1916</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Grouvelle, 1916" authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1916" box="[502,841,1339,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Macrostolops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singularis">
<emphasis box="[502,651,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M. singularis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grouvelle, A." box="[658,841,1339,1366]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="234 - 256" refId="ref105215" refString="Grouvelle, A. (1916) Descriptions des Clavicornes nouveaux de la Republique Argentine. Revista del Museo de La Plata, 23, 234 - 256." type="journal article" year="1916">Grouvelle, 1916</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) seems to make it possible to recognize these species in additional new specimens when they are available. The 
<typeStatus box="[831,879,1375,1401]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
species should be deposited in the Museo de la Plata (Facultad de Ciencias Naturales y Museo, 
<collectingRegion box="[701,854,1411,1438]" country="Argentina" name="Ciudad Autonoma de Buenos Aires" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Buenos Aires</collectingRegion>
) and Muséum national d’Histoire naturelle (Paris), however, at least in the latter collection no specimen of these species has been found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
